																								 New Delhi, Nov. 19: Parthasarthi Shome, co-chairman of the joint working group on goods and services tax (GST), has said the proposed GST structure could have a dual format at the central and state levels. We have in our own mind some ideas ... (on) how we might be able to roll out (GST) or what the overall structure would be. Lets hope we can have central and state GST in dual format, Shome said.																								 Mumbai, Nov. 19: The income-tax department has issued a notice to Tata Industries on tax matters related to buying the AT amp;T stake in Idea Cellular. We have submitted all the details, a spokesperson said.																								 Mumbai, Nov. 19: The RBI has made it easier for persons suffering from mental illnesses such as autism and cerebral palsy to open accounts by asking banks to accept guardianship certificates issued by local level committees set up under the National Trust Act.																								 New Delhi, Nov. 19: French firm Carrefour is planning to set up shop in India by 2009 with a wholly owned wholesale retail business and expects to finalise a partner for its hyperstores in four months.																								 New Delhi, Nov. 19: The Telecom Disputes Settlement and Appellate Tribunal has rejected a contempt application filed by Reliance Communications against the COAI, for allegedly taking the legal battle on spectrum on a media trial.
